@startuml
title IntentSpecification mandatory profile proposal

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

rectangle "TMF921 IntentSpecification\nbase resource model" as TMF #EEF2FF

rectangle "Platform mandatory profile\nTMF-aligned, not TMF-minimal" as PROFILE #E8F5E9

TMF --> PROFILE : platform conformance\nadds lifecycle-aware rules

rectangle "DRAFT IntentSpecification" as DRAFT #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "Minimum mandatory fields\n\n- id\n- href\n- name\n- familyId\n- version\n- lifecycleStatus = DRAFT\n- isBundle\n- @type\n- @baseType" as DRAFT_FIELDS
  rectangle "Allowed to be incomplete\nwhile authored" as DRAFT_INCOMPLETE
}

rectangle "Activation gate" as GATE #FFE0B2 {
  rectangle "Validate ACTIVE profile\n\nReject with 422 if required\nACTIVE fields are missing" as VALIDATE
}

rectangle "ACTIVE IntentSpecification" as ACTIVE #E0F2F1 {
  rectangle "Minimum mandatory fields\n\nDRAFT mandatory fields plus:\n- validFor.startDateTime\n- expressionSpecification\n- expressionSpecification.iri\n- expressionSpecification.expressionLanguage\n- targetEntitySchema\n- specCharacteristic" as ACTIVE_FIELDS
  rectangle "Published runtime contract\nfor discovery, governance,\nvalidation, and resolution" as ACTIVE_CONTRACT
}

rectangle "Runtime intent processing\nseparate API decision" as RUNTIME #F3E5F5 {
  rectangle "Runtime request may reference\nintentSpecification.id\nor may be resolved by\nexpression.iri if unambiguous" as RUNTIME_RULE
}

PROFILE --> DRAFT : create / edit as DRAFT
DRAFT --> GATE : request activation
GATE --> ACTIVE : profile satisfied
GATE -[#red,dashed]-> DRAFT : missing required ACTIVE fields
ACTIVE --> RUNTIME : provides active semantic\nand validation contract

note right of ACTIVE
expressionSpecification is mandatory
when expressionSpecification.iri
is mandatory.

targetEntitySchema is the
machine-readable validation contract.

specCharacteristic is the
catalogue/governance view.
end note

note bottom of RUNTIME
This diagram captures the proposal only.
Runtime intent resolution rules belong
in a separate runtime/API decision.
end note

@enduml
